AS TO COUNT 1 AND 2:  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.    Defendant sentenced to serve 9 MONTHS, as to each count, in the House of Correction; release privileges for work and treatment.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 18 MONTHS.
Conditions:  
*  Letter of apology to JM Remodeling.
*  AODA assessment/treatment deemed appropriate.
*  Mental health evaluation/treatment deemed appropriate.
*  No contact with JM Remodeling.
*  Absolute sobriety; random urine screens;
*  Pay DNA surcharge, costs, fees and any other surcharges; if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.

Upon successful completion, Court finds that expungement will not unduly depreciate the seriousness of the offense.

Appeal rights given.

Filed:
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
Victim /Witness/Restitution Worksheet.

AS TO COUNTS 1 AND 2:  Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to her plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived her rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.
